        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-05T22:48:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "doc says \"If callback finishes running, Run will return the error it returned.\", but this returns a multi-error.\n\ni don\u0027t see the value of returning a multi error if serverErr is not nil. In this case, it seems `done` would return a context.Canceled error. i think we should return serverErr if it is not nil. Otherwise return the error from done.\n\nstepping back, it would be simpler to do\n  \n  case err :\u003d \u003c-s.errC:\n\tcancel()\n\t\u003c-done\n\treturn err\n\nthen we don\u0027t need the loop.\nAnd then, we also don\u0027t need the panic",
      "revId": "dea82ff63cade326c2f1e6ac1a35792a643ac20c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
